<Recipe>
  <Title image="Quick Andouille Gumbo_AndouilleGumbo.jpg" name="Quick Andouille Gumbo" category="SOUP" cuisine="CAJUN">
    <Yield amount="4" units="SERVING"/>
    <Times prep="10" cook="30"/>
  </Title>
  <Nutrition calories="" fat="" carbs="" protein="" sugar="" sodium="" fiber="" servings="1" servingsUnit="CUP"/>
  <Description>This isn't a true gumbo as it lacks okra.  You could add it if you like.  You could add chicken too.

It's rather important to use the same pan from start to finish, preferably a large sauté pan.  You're gonna cook some stuff, remove and hold, cook some more stuff in the oil left behind, remove and hold, etc.  At each step you are building on the flavors of the step before, adding as little extra fat as possible.  Eventually everything returns to that pan to come together in a rich, deep, complex flavored sauce. </Description>
