  <Method>
    <Step image="">Chop peppers to a small dice.</Step>
    <Step image="">Sauté sausage until browned. Transfer to a bowl to hold. </Step>
    <Step image="">Add peppers and onions to skillet, add butter (if necessary) and sauté until lightly caramelized. Transfer to bowl with sausage. </Step>
    <Step image="">Whisk in chicken stock and roux, bring to a boil.</Step>
    <Step image="">Add tomato concasse, previously cooked sausage and browned vegetables.  </Step>
    <Step image="">Add garlic, Picapeppa sauce, bay leaf, thyme, and 3/4 of the parsley.  </Step>
    <Step image="">Reduce heat to simmer, cook for 15-20 minutes, until sauce thickens to syrup consistency. </Step>
    <Step image="">Add salt and pepper, Tabasco to taste. </Step>
    <Step image="">Serve with &lt;a href='/GetRecipe?recipeName=Cajun%20Rice'&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Cajun Rice&lt;/a&gt; and some Filé powder.</Step>
  </Method>
